{"key":"post-8491975","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8491975</id>\n<content>Quite frankly, with dunking, I see little benefit to a casing layer on manure, coir, compost or straw, as long as &lt;i&gt;P cubensis&lt;/i&gt; is all you're growing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Mist as required right through harvest.&amp;nbsp; Misting doesn't cause aborts.&amp;nbsp; Primordia and small pins get baptised by thunderstorms in texas and florida that literally dump buckets of water on them and they don't abort.&amp;nbsp; Misting, and then sealing up in an improperly-built fruiting chamber with no air exchange will definitely cause aborts.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Fan well after each misting and you'll be fine.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8492040</next>\n<prev>8491874</prev>\n<first>8491818</first>\n<last>8492040</last>\n<when>1212763814</when>\n<utime>06/06/08 05:50 PM</utime>\n</post>"}